editorialNotes.standard: Shooting movies on film may be a dying art, but just because we live in the digital age doesn’t mean we have to abandon our analogue past. We get warm, nostalgic fuzzies from 8mm Vintage Camera’s grainy, flickery film filters and lens effects, conjuring up memories of vacation travelogues screened in wood-panelled basements. It’s not just about old-school kicks, though—this powerful suite of tools can give any video an authentic period look.
editorialNotes.short: The easy way to create authentic vintage movies.

editorialNotes.tagline: Turn any room into an anatomy lab

editorialNotes.standard: With a suite of powerful tools, touch-screen controls, gorgeous templates and customisable effects, this full-featured editor is in a class of its own. Plus, with iCloud Drive, you can edit on your iPhone, iPad or Mac, wherever you are.
editorialNotes.short: Make your pictures shine with this set of photography tools.

ios.subtitle: Talking Cats Pet Sim for Kids

editorialNotes.standard: The moment we met wee kitty Crumbs in Little Kitten, we let out an audible “awww.” This adorable digital feline encourages children to play and explore, interacting with the lively toys and simple games in Crumbs’ room. We’re amazed by the cinematic animation, and appreciate the sleep timer that sends Crumbs to bed when our kids’ screen time is over.
editorialNotes.short: Embark on exciting adventures with your own kitty pal.

editorialNotes.standard: This writing app is designed to let you type without distraction. Key features we’ve come to depend on include the customisable keyboard, iCloud sync and its streamlined interface for easy document preview and access.
